Create a new InteRactModel object

Source: R/InteRactModel.R
interact.Rd

Create a new InteRactModel object by specifying dictionary and equation names available from the actdata package.

Usage

interact(
  dictionary = list("usfullsurveyor2015", "all"),
  equations = list("us2010", "all")
)

Arguments

dictionary

(character) dictionary name and group. The default is set to list("usfullsurveyor2015", "all").

See available options using actdata::dataset_keys()

equations

(character) equations name and group. The default is set to list("usfullsurveyor2015", "all").

See available options using actdata::equations

Currently only equations with "equation_type == impressionabo" are valid.

Value

An InteRactModel object.

Examples

act <- interact(
  dictionary = list(dataset = "indiana2003", group = "all"),
  equations = list(key = "nc1978", group = "male")
)
